U.K. Stocks Drop After U.S. Employers Add Fewest Workers in Eight Months

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-06-03T12:33:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/u-k-stocks-drop-after-u-s-employers-add-fewest-workers-in-eight-months.html
U.K. stocks declined after a
government report showed U.S. employers added the fewest number
of workers in eight months and unemployment unexpectedly rose to
9.1 percent.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index slid 23.21, or 0.4 percent, to
5,824.71 as of 1:33 p.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Adam Haigh at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net  